[13:08] <brrt> samcv: the problem is that x86 'jump' instructions can take one-byte, two-byte, or four-byte address offsets
[13:08] <brrt> dynasm, in a vain attempt to be clever, tries to use the minimum amount of bytes
[13:08] <brrt> but there is a problem
